INSERT INTO design_image_generations VALUES(9,'f8fa5777-3543-4eb7-90fe-efd53fef0097',2,replace('**1. Color Scheme:**\n\nOpt for a neutral palette to create a sense of space and tranquility. Use Dulux color codes.\n\n- Main color: Soft Pebble (00NN 72/000) – a soft, light grey for walls.\n- Accent color: Chic Shadow (00NN 31/000) – a darker grey for the vanity or accent wall.\n- Highlight color: Copper Blush (Copper Blush 50YR 36/263) – for accessories and decor.\n\n**2. Layout Suggestions:**\n\nGiven that we are working with a small bathroom, arrange your fixtures linearly. Install the sink and vanity opposite to the toilet and shower to allow free movement. Consider a frameless glass shower enclosure to create the illusion of more space.\n\n**3. Material Recommendations:**\n\n- Flooring: Use large format porcelain tiles in a light grey (similar to Soft Pebble) to reflect light. These are easily available in the UAE.\n- Walls: Paint most walls in Soft Pebble. Consider a Chic Shadow tiled accent wall in the shower area.\n- Vanity: A floating vanity in Chic Shadow with a quartz countertop to maximize floor space.\n\n**4. Furniture List:**\n\n- Vanity: IKEA GODMORGON / ODENSVIK sink cabinet (AED 995)\n- Toilet: Kohler’s Ove One-piece toilet (AED 1,500)\n- Shower enclosure: Kludi''s Frameless Glass Shower Enclosure (AED 2,000)\n\n**5. Lighting Plan:**\n\n- Main lighting: Recessed LED ceiling lights, like Philips Hue White Ambiance (AED 200 each)\n- Accent lighting: A backlit mirror above the vanity, such as IKEA STORJORM (AED 395)\n\n**6. Decor Elements:**\n\n- Accessories: Copper accents like soap dispenser, toothbrush holder from Crate and Barrel (AED 100-200 each)\n- Artwork: A small, framed Arabic calligraphy print from Gallery One (AED 300)\n- Plants: An indoor succulent from Dubai Garden Centre (AED 50-100)\n\n**7. Shopping List:**\n\n- Dulux Paints: Available at ACE Hardware stores across the UAE.\n- Porcelain tiles, vanity, and fixtures: IKEA, Kohler or Kludi showrooms.\n- Decor and accessories: Crate and Barrel, Gallery One, and Dubai Garden Centre.\n\n**8. Timeline:**\n\n- Week 1-2: Finalize and purchase all materials, furniture, and decor.\n- Week 3-4: Start with painting, tiling, and lighting installation.\n- Week 5: Install fixtures and finishes.\n- Week 6: Add decor elements and final touches.\n\nRemember, due to Dubai''s hot climate, opt for materials that can withstand high temperatures and humidity levels. The design is modern but considers local culture through subtle elements like Arabic artwork.','\n',char(10)),'Small modern bathroom','[]','[]',3,'completed','[{"url":"https:\/\/oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net\/private\/org-ilhWWDzx0WN6WdBJ9SUU5Xsl\/user-t1vqMPzgD9oUSWDBmz7H0TI0\/img-8pfSI9xHkqlGjXatssb3U5Wu.png?st=2025-08-20T15%3A39%3A24Z&se=2025-08-20T17%3A39%3A24Z&sp=r&sv=2024-08-04&sr=b&rscd=inline&rsct=image\/png&skoid=ed3ea2f9-5e38-44be-9a1b-7c1e65e4d54f&sktid=a48cca56-e6da-484e-a814-9c849652bcb3&skt=2025-08-20T00%3A19%3A54Z&ske=2025-08-21T00%3A19%3A54Z&sks=b&skv=2024-08-04&sig=ABRwWWunXWnuedJa6dMKrNkKYYHtJu2QjUBlb0TJ1Ak%3D","prompt":"Wide angle view, A beautiful modern interior space interior design in Dubai, UAE. High-quality architectural visualization with natural daylight. Clean, elegant space with attention to detail. Photorealistic rendering, interior design photography style. Luxurious finishes suitable for Dubai market. Incorporating elements: Small modern bathroom","index":1},{"url":"https:\/\/oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net\/private\/org-ilhWWDzx0WN6WdBJ9SUU5Xsl\/user-t1vqMPzgD9oUSWDBmz7H0TI0\/img-sgJ4YJv48aYtzBo9uXQ4kEJO.png?st=2025-08-20T15%3A39%3A40Z&se=2025-08-20T17%3A39%3A40Z&sp=r&sv=2024-08-04&sr=b&rscd=inline&rsct=image\/png&skoid=f1dafa11-a0c2-4092-91d4-10981fbda051&sktid=a48cca56-e6da-484e-a814-9c849652bcb3&skt=2025-08-20T14%3A06%3A03Z&ske=2025-08-21T14%3A06%3A03Z&sks=b&skv=2024-08-04&sig=KBcNghzVGNLjW3NGDDstoo5RqfkURh2zLbuKyKyjm1g%3D","prompt":"Close-up detail shot,