INSERT INTO design_image_generations VALUES(10,'e3cff39f-001c-4c87-8758-304d17d421be',2,replace('**1. Color Scheme**\nThe palette will be based on neutral colors. For the walls, use Jotun''s Soothing Beige (1024) and for the accents like doors and trim, go for Jotun''s Elegant White (1001). To add a pop of color, opt for Jotun''s Dusty Red (20120) in selected areas. \n\n**2. Layout Suggestions**\nFor the living room, arrange seating around a central coffee table for conversation and entertaining. Use a large area rug to define the space. Place a large sofa against the longest wall and add two armchairs opposite it. The dining room should be near the kitchen for convenient serving. Opt for a rectangular table to accommodate more people and flank it with a buffet table for additional storage.\n\n**3. Material Recommendations**\nUse marble for flooring as it''s abundant in UAE and suits the hot climate. Use TINO''s Beige Marble. For wall finishes, use textured plaster in beige color to match the flooring. For the dining room, consider a feature wall with Al Ain''s decorative stone cladding.\n\n**4. Furniture List**\n- Sofa: Ikea''s KIVIK Sofa, around AED 2,500\n- Armchairs: Ikea''s STRANDMON Wing chair, around AED 1,000/each\n- Coffee Table: Marina Home''s HEMINGWAY Coffee Table, around AED 3,000\n- Dining Table: Crate and Barrel''s PARSONS Dining Table, around AED 4,000\n- Dining Chairs: Ikea''s VOLFGANG Chair, around AED 500/each\n- Buffet Table: Crate and Barrel''s CIRQUE Three-Door Sideboard, around AED 6,000\n\n**5. Lighting Plan**\nUse a combination of general, task, and accent lighting. For general lighting, install LED downlights from Philips. For task lighting, place floor lamps from Ikea near the sofa and armchairs. For accent lighting, use wall sconces from Marina Home on either side of your large artwork or mirror.\n\n**6. Decor Elements**\nIncorporate local artwork from Alserkal Avenue galleries and indoor plants like snake plant and ZZ plant from Dubai Garden Centre. Use Persian rugs from National Iranian Carpets to add an exotic touch. \n\n**7. Shopping List**\nMost items can be found at Ikea, Marina Home, Crate and Barrel, Dubai Garden Centre, and Alserkal Avenue. The total cost should be around AED 70,000 - 80,000, well within your budget.\n\n**8. Timeline**\nThe project can be completed in 4-6 weeks. Begin with ordering furniture and scheduling delivery. Next, start on floor and wall finish installations. Once finished, bring in furniture, set up lighting, and finally, add decor elements. \n\nThis plan balances modern design with eco-friendly elements, keeping in mind Dubai''s climate and local resources. It also respects the local culture with its use of local artwork and Persian rugs.','\n',char(10)),'Aosfijosifjoiff','["living_room","dining_room"]','["modern","eco_friendly"]',3,'completed','[{"url":"https:\/\/oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net\/private\/org-ilhWWDzx0WN6WdBJ9SUU5Xsl\/user-t1vqMPzgD9oUSWDBmz7H0TI0\/img-ehy7fCrUGDz1que9rTJogYMd.png?st=2025-08-20T15%3A44%3A44Z&se=2025-08-20T17%3A44%3A44Z&sp=r&sv=2024-08-04&sr=b&rscd=inline&rsct=image\/png&skoid=8b33a531-2df9-46a3-bc02-d4b1430a422c&sktid=a48cca56-e6da-484e-a814-9c849652bcb3&skt=2025-08-20T07%3A59%3A19Z&ske=2025-08-21T07%3A59%3A19Z&sks=b&skv=2024-08-04&sig=Or6n%2B3sMkBwOZaxheuaHqoUKbPBF%2BjSxr1GbssWvsqI%3D","prompt":"Wide angle view, A beautiful modern and eco_friendly living_room, dining_room interior design in Dubai, UAE. High-quality architectural visualization with natural daylight. Clean, elegant space with attention to detail. Photorealistic rendering, interior design photography style. Luxurious finishes suitable for Dubai market. ","index":1},{"url":"https:\/\/oaidalleapiprodscus.blob.core.windows.net\/private\/org-ilhWWDzx0WN6WdBJ9SUU5Xsl\/user-t1vqMPzgD9oUSWDBmz7H0TI0\/img-jgwKJuIo23Yvjte7oiT057ta.png?st=2025-08-20T15%3A45%3A01Z&se=2025-08-20T17%3A45%3A01Z&sp=r&sv=2024-08-04&sr=b&rscd=inline&rsct=image\/png&skoid=8b33a531-2df9-46a3