INSERT INTO design_image_generations VALUES(12,'74598a60-3019-4db0-918d-a445aff6abce',2,replace('**1. Color Scheme:**\nThe color palette for this project will be a blend of industrial grays and classic whites and beiges. \n\n- Base color: Sherwin Williams Pure White SW 7005\n- Accent color 1: Sherwin Williams Cityscape SW 7067 (Industrial Gray)\n- Accent color 2: Sherwin Williams Agreeable Gray SW 7029 (Classic Beige)\n\n**2. Layout Suggestions:**\nThe bedroom should ideally be spacious, with the bed positioned centrally and a seating area by the window. The dining room should have a large dining table in the center, with a sideboard against the wall for storage and display.\n\n**3. Material Recommendations:**\n- Flooring: Polished concrete for the industrial vibe, available from Arteco in Dubai.\n- Wall finishes: Exposed brick wall in the dining room and plastered white walls in the bedroom, both available from Baniyas Building Materials Company LLC.\n- Window coverings: White or beige linen curtains, available from Homes R Us.\n\n**4. Furniture List:**\n- Bedroom: \n  - Industrial style bed: 2,000 AED\n  - Two bedside tables: 500 AED each\n  - Seating area: 1,500 AED\n- Dining Room:\n  - Large wooden dining table: 3,000 AED\n  - Six dining chairs: 500 AED each\n  - Sideboard: 1,500 AED\n\n**5. Lighting Plan:**\n- Bedroom: Recessed ceiling lights and a couple of industrial-style bedside lamps.\n- Dining Room: A classic chandelier over the dining table and wall-mounted lights for the sideboard.\n\n**6. Decor Elements:**\n- Bedroom: Large mirror, a few framed black and white photographs, a classic Persian rug.\n- Dining Room: A centerpiece for the dining table, a large mirror over the sideboard, and some classic artworks on the walls.\n\n**7. Shopping List:**\nMost of the items can be purchased from local suppliers such as Homes R Us, Pan Emirates, and IKEA. For unique industrial and classic pieces, you can visit the Al Quoz industrial area.\n\n**8. Timeline:**\nThe project can be completed in 2-3 months, depending on the availability of the items. It''s recommended to start with the structural work (flooring, wall finishes), then move on to the furniture, lighting, and finally the decor elements.\n\nThis plan combines industrial and classic elements, while considering Dubai''s climate (using durable materials that can withstand high temperatures) and cultural preferences (classic artworks, Persian rug). It also provides a practical and achievable budget range, utilizing local suppliers in the UAE.','\n',char(10)),'Adijofoiajsfijfij','["bedroom","dining_room"]','["industrial","classic"]',3,'processing',NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 16:51:13',NULL,'2025-08-20 16:51:11','2025-08-20 16:51:13');
INSERT INTO design_image_generations VALUES(13,'83ed4961-5b0d-49ae-940d-bf9ed43730c8',2,replace('**1. Color Scheme:**\n- Primary: Charcoal Grey (#36454F)\n- Secondary: Warm Cream (#F5F5DC)\n- Accent: Burnt Sienna (#E97451), Brushed Gold (#DAA520)\n\n**2. Layout Suggestions:**\n- Bedroom: Create a focal point with a large bed against the main wall. Add side tables on both sides. Space permitting, include a seating area with a chair and a small table.\n- Dining Room: Center the dining table in the room. If space allows, create a buffet area with a side table and overhead shelving.\n\n**3. Material Recommendations:**\n- Flooring: Consider polished concrete flooring for an industrial feel. This can be sourced from local suppliers like "Super Cement Manufacturing Co. LLC".\n- Walls: Exposed brick walls can add to the industrial look. For a less dramatic approach, the walls can be painted in the primary color. \n\n**4. Furniture List:**\n- Bedroom: \n  - Industrial-style iron bed (approx 2500 AED)\n  - Matching side tables (approx 500 AED each)\n  - Classic-style chair (approx 1000 AED)\n- Dining Room:\n  - Solid wood dining table (approx 3000 AED)\n  - 6 Leather upholstered chairs (approx 3000 AED for set)\n  - Classic side table (approx 1500 AED)\n\n**5. Lighting Plan:**\n- Bedroom: Industrial-style pendant lights for bedside lamps. Add a classic chandelier for ambient lighting.\n- Dining Room: Industrial-style pendant lights over the dining table and buffet area.\n\n**6. Decor Elements:**\n- Bedroom: Oversized classic-style mirror, cream curtains, artwork with warm tones, large indoor plant like a Fiddle Leaf Fig.\n- Dining Room: Oversized classic-style mirror, cream curtains, artwork with warm tones, large indoor plant like a Monstera.\n\n**7. Shopping List:**\n- "Dragon Mart" for lighting fixtures, curtains, and decor elements.\n- "IKEA" for bed, side tables, and chairs.\n- "Home Centre" for dining table, side table, and artwork.\n- "Dubai Garden Centre" for indoor plants.\n\n**8. Timeline:**\n- Weeks 1-2: Procurement of materials and furniture\n- Week 3: Flooring and wall finish installation\n- Week 4: Furniture arrangement and lighting installation\n- Week 5: Decor elements placement and final touches\n\nThis design plan combines industrial and classic styles while respecting the local climate and culture. The natural materials and color scheme provide a warm and inviting feel. The cream and gold accents help to soften the industrial elements and tie the look together. It offers practicality and style within the given budget.','\n',char(10)),'Adijofoiajsfijfij','["bedroom","dining_room"]','["industrial","classic"]',3,'pending',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2025-08-20 16:52:46','2025-08-20 16:52:46');
